'''Uncomplicated Firewall''' (ufw) is a [[Firewall (computing)|firewall]] that is designed to be easy to use. It uses a [[command line interface]] consisting of a small number of simple commands, and uses [[iptables]] for configuration.
==GUI for Uncomplicated Firewall== {{Infobox software | name = Gufw (GUI for Uncomplicated Firewall) | logo = | screenshot = [[File:Gufw 10.04.4.png|355px]] | caption = | collapsible = | author = Gufw Developers | developer = | released = | latest release version = [http://packages.ubuntu.com/natty/gufw 11.04.2] | latest release date = April, 2011 | latest preview version = | latest preview date = | frequently updated = With every Ubuntu release | programming language = [[Python (programming language)|Python]] | operating system = [[Linux]] | platform = | size = | language = More languages [https://translations.launchpad.net/gui-ufw] | status = Active | genre = | license = [[GNU General Public License]] | website = http://gufw.tuxfamily.org }}
'''GUI for Uncomplicated Firewall''' (Gufw) is, as the name states, a [[graphical user interface]] for UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall). It has been designed for [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]].
Gufw is intended to be an easy, intuitive, way to manage an Ubuntu [[Firewall (computing)|firewall]]. It supports common tasks such as allowing or blocking pre-configured, common [[Peer-to-peer|P2P]], or individual ports. Gufw is powered by UFW, runs on Ubuntu, and anywhere else [[Python (programming language)|Python]], [[GTK]], and UFW are available.
